A matatu driver died in Eldoret on Thursday following an accident involving a police officer at Kapsoya. Sylvester Chumba sustained serious injuries at the area AP camp after the officer allegedly hit his car from behind.  He died while being treated at Moi Teaching and Referral Hospital. Amid claims the officer attacked the victim, Chumba's brother Frankline Kirwa said the family wants proper investigations. Uasin Gishu AP commander Daniel Rukunga said they had not received a report on the incident but that a probe would be conducted. Click here for the latest political stories  